# First-party SHACL Rules case: cyclic data with a self-feeding symmetric rule.
# The data is a directed 3-cycle (alice -> bob -> carol -> alice) on ex:knows.
# The rule derives the reverse edge for every ex:knows edge. The closure is
# value-preserving over the finite node set {alice, bob, carol}, so the fixpoint
# terminates despite the cycle; it adds the three reverse edges.

@prefix ex: <http://example.org/ns#> .
@prefix sh: <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#> .

ex:alice ex:knows ex:bob .
ex:bob   ex:knows ex:carol .
ex:carol ex:knows ex:alice .

ex:SymmetricKnows
  a sh:NodeShape ;
  sh:targetSubjectsOf ex:knows ;
  sh:rule [ a sh:TripleRule ;
            sh:subject [ sh:path ex:knows ] ;
            sh:predicate ex:knows ;
            sh:object sh:this ] .
